<HEADLINE>
JESSE VENTURA BACK ON BOULEVARD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Will move in the ``n'' California, ``a'' national and ``k''
editorial news files.) 
(EDITORS: Dennis McCarthy is a columnist for the Los Angeles Daily
News) 
BY DENNIS McCARTHY  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ It used to be simple covering politicians on the
run.
</P>
<P>
   You'd wait until their bodyguards jumped out of the dark
government sedans, then look for the shortest, frailest guy. That
was the politician.
</P>
<P>
   Not anymore.
</P>
<P>
   Jesse Ventura, the governor-elect of Minnesota, jumped out of
the back seat of his sedan in front of Jerry's Famous Deli on the
boulevard in suburban Studio City on Tuesday afternoon and stood
