   FED-RATES-ANALYSIS (Washington) _ The Federal Reserves' decision
Tuesday to cut interest rates again marks the completion of a
three-part strategy cobbled together over the past seven weeks by
the Clinton administration and Alan Greenspan, the Fed's chairman,
to insulate the American economy from the worst effects of global
economic turmoil, which only a few weeks ago seemed on the brink of
exploding into something far worse. By David E. Sanger.
</P>
