   SCI-DINOSAUR-SKIN (Undated) _ For the first time,
paleontologists have found fossilized embryos of dinosaurs so well
preserved that their delicate skin has survived in mineralized
form, providing a glimpse of reptilian scales in patterns bearing a
family resemblance to the skin of modern-day lizards. By John Noble
Wilford.
