<P>
   &UR; IS THIS A GOOD TIME TO BE IN THE STOCK MARKET? &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   The market's turmoil over the past few months has unnerved
almost everyone. People want to know:
</P>
<P>
   _ When will the turbulence end?
</P>
<P>
   _ Is the stock market safe?
</P>
<P>
   _ What are some good mutual funds to buy now?
</P>
<P>
   Steven T. Goldberg, associate editor of Kiplinger's Personal
Finance Magazine, answers these questions and others in two
articles adapted from his new book ``But Which Mutual Funds?'' _
 &UR; AVAILABLE FREE TO MOST NEWSPAPERS. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   In Part One, Goldberg explains why this could be the best time
to get into the market, then offers a formula for determining how
much of your money to invest in the stock market to reach certain
goals, such as a comfortable retirement. In Part Two, he lists
specific mutual funds that can help you achieve those goals.
</P>
