pop concert industry and its theatrical touring trade. By Peter G.
Gosselin. (2 takes; f and e coding) GRAPHIC: 25 picas x 11 inches,
``$1 billion acquisition spree.''
</P>
<P>
   TELECOM-VALLEY (Undated) ) -- When telecommunications
entrepreneurs are encouraged to go west, they're not going to
Silicon Valley. They're heading straight to Westford, Mass. to
develop the next generation of switches, software and high-tech
tools for the nation's communications infrastructure. By Ronald
Rosenberg. 1400 words.
