   &UR; Other financial &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TRADE-REPORT (Washington) _ The trade deficit in goods and
services narrowed in September, shrinking from August's record
shortfall. The trade gap was $14.03 billion, down from August's
revised $15.9 billion. Exports of goods and services rose 2.3
percent in September, led by a record surge in shipments of
commercial aircraft. Imports fell 0.2 percent, mainly reflecting
weaker demand for oil and industrial products. By country, the
merchandise deficit with Japan narrowed to $5.07 billion in
September from $5.2 billion in August and $5.1 billion a year
earlier. By David E. Sanger.
</P>
<P>
   LIVENT (New York) _ Developments as Livent, the Broadway theater
company, continues considering seeking bankruptcy protection or
other possible solutions to its financial troubles. By Melody
Petersen.
</P>
