   MIDEAST-ECON (Undated) _ Paralleling the peace process, and
being pushed by the United States, the Jordanians, Israelis and
Palestinians (and tangentially the Egyptians) are beginning to
discuss regional trade and investment plans. By William A. Orme Jr.
</P>
<P>
   BRAZIL-ECON (Rio de Janeiro) _ Reflecting the central bank's
tightening in September, Brazil's gross domestic product fell 1.5
percent in the third quarter from the prior three months and 0.1
percent from the year-earlier period. By Larry Rohter.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At 1:10 p.m., the industrial average was up
28 points, and the Nasdaq index up 16. Elsewhere, prices rose 1.3
percent in Tokyo and 0.6 percent in Hong Kong. They fell 0.4
percent in Frankfurt but rose 0.1 percent in London. Shares gained
1.8 percent in Brazil and 0.3 percent in Mexico. On the American
debt market, the long bond was up 24/32 point at midday. By Robert
D. Hershey.
</P>
