camcorder, cell phone, laptop. Why don't they last as long as
they're supposed to? Why don't they improve as fast as other parts
of gadgets? The answer is the complicated slurry of chemical energy
that each rechargeable power pack contains. With potential small
how graphic. By Michel Marriott.
