<HEADER>
A6946 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-JELL-O-HOLIDAYS-3rdTa     11-18 0790
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JELL-O-HOLIDAYS-3rdTake-TEX </SLUG>
 
UNDATED: Granbury, Texas 
<TEXT>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   CRANBERRY JELL-O SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Serves 10-12
</P>
<P>
   6-ounce package raspberry Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   15-ounce can crushed pineapple
</P>
<P>
   8-ounce container large-curd cottage cheese, drained
</P>
<P>
   16-ounce can cranberry sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup pecans, chopped
</P>
<P>
   8 ounces cream cheese, softened
</P>
<P>
   Drain pineapple, reserving liquid. Add water to make 1 1/2 cups
total liquid. Prepare Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water, as directed
on package, except instead of the 2 cups cold water called for on
package, add the 1 1/2 cups liquid from above.
</P>
<P>
   Pour into 9-by-13-inch glass dish and refrigerate until
partially set, about 1 hour.
</P>
<P>
   Combine remaining ingredients except cream cheese and place in
refrigerator while Jell-O is partially setting. When it is ready,
add chilled ingredients and return to refrigerator until solidly
set.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, whip softened cream cheese with just enough milk (1
to 2 tablespoons) to make it easy to spread. Spread on top of salad
after salad is firm. Return to refrigerator to firm up the cream
cheese.
</P>
<P>
   Cut into squares and serve on a lettuce leaf.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 246 calories, 10 grams fat, 30
grams carbohydrates, 10 grams protein, 22 milligrams cholesterol,
93 milligrams sodium, 37 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Pat Cantrell, Fort Worth. Texas
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   RED &AMP; GREEN HOLIDAY SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Serves 12-16
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce package lime Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   15-ounce can pineapple chunks, drained (reserve juice)
</P>
<P>
   2 cups miniature marshmallows
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce package lemon Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   8-ounce package cream cheese, cubed
</P>
<P>
   1 envelope Dream Whip, prepared
</P>
<P>
   1 jar dark, sweet cherries, drained (reserve juice)
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce package black cherry Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   Sliced almonds, for garnish
</P>
<P>
   Prepare lime Jell-O and add drained pineapple. Pat into
9-by-13-inch glass dish. Chill until firm. Add water to reserved
pineapple juice to make 1 cup. heat to boiling and add
marshmallows, lemon Jell-O and cream cheese, in that order, and
stir until all are dissolved thoroughly. Cool mixture and add
prepared Dream Whip. Pour lemon mixture over lime Jell-O, and chill
until firm. Add water to cherry juice to make 1 cups. Substitute
cherry juice for one of the cups of water in the preparation of the
black cherry Jell-O. Add cherries, and chill until slightly
thickened. Pour over lemon mixture. Chill until firm. Top with
sliced almonds before serving, if desired.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 165 calories, 5 grams fat, 23
grams carbohydrates, 7 grams protein, 16 milligrams cholesterol, 73
milligrams sodium, 30 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Dorothy Horton, Granbury
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   ORANGE CHEESE SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce package orange Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   1 cup boiling water
</P>
<P>
   8-ounce can crushed pineapple, drained
</P>
<P>
   1 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 cup heavy cream, whipped
</P>
<P>
   1 cup grated American cheese
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chopped pecans
</P>
<P>
   Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir in drained pineapple and
sugar. When almost set, fold in the whipped cream. Fold in the
cheese and the nuts. Chill until firm. This is particularly good
with ham.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 407 calories, 26 grams fat, 39
grams carbohydrates, 9 grams protein, 55 milligrams cholesterol,
232 milligrams sodium, 56 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Zoe Tankursley, Weatherford, Texas
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Unmolding your masterpiece
</P>
<P>
   Moisten your fingertip and gently pull gelatin from top edge of
mold. Or, use a small metal spatula dipped in warm water.
</P>
<P>
   Dip the mold in warm, not hot, water just to the rim, for about
15 seconds.
</P>
<P>
   Lift mold from water, hold upright, and shake to loosen the
gelatin. Or, gently pull gelatin from edge of mold.
</P>
<P>
   Moisten chilled serving plate with water. (This allows gelatin
to be moved after unmolding.) Hold serving plate and mold firmly
together; quickly turn mold upside down onto plate.
</P>
<P>
   Invert mold and plate; holding mold and plate together, shake
slightly to loosen.
</P>
<P>
   Gently remove mold. If gelatin does not release easily, dip mold
in warm water again for a few seconds. Remove mold; center gelatin
on serving plate.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Celebrating molds
</P>
<P>
   To mark America's holiday ties with Jell-O, Kraft has published
``The Joy of Jell-O Molds: 56 Festive Recipes from the Classic to
the Contemporary.'' Recipes include gazpacho molds, cucumber sour
cream mold, orange blossom mold and kir royale mold. If you can
tear yourself away from the family's traditional offerings to try
other recipes, the book can be ordered by sending a check for $8
payable to The Joy of Jell-O Molds Recipes Book, Box 5428, Clinton,
IA 52736-5428.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
