<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   MERRY BERRY SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Serves 15-18
</P>
<P>
   6-ounce package raspberry gelatin
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups boiling water
</P>
<P>
   2 10-ounce packages frozen raspberries
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   1 pint sour cream
</P>
<P>
   6-ounce package cherry gelatin
</P>
<P>
   1 cup boiling water
</P>
<P>
   15-ounce can crushed pineapple
</P>
<P>
   16-ounce can whole-berry cranberry sauce
</P>
<P>
   Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 1/2 cups boiling water. Add
frozen raspberries and lemon juice, stirring until thawed. Pour
into a 13-by-9-inch pan or a ring mold. Refrigerate until firm.
When firm, cover with sour cream.
</P>
<P>
   Dissolve cherry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water; add remaining
ingredients. Chill until slightly thickened, then pour on top of
sour-cream layer. Chill thoroughly.
</P>
<P>
   If making this in a pan instead of mold, cut into squares to
serve. It looks nicer this way than spooned out of the pan.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 285 calories, 9 grams fat, 42
grams carbohydrates, 12 grams protein, 17 milligrams cholesterol,
79 milligrams sodium, 28 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Kelly Greene, Benbrook, Texas
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   MANDARIN ORANGE JELL-O RING
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6-8
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce box lemon Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce box orange Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   2 cups boiling water
</P>
<P>
   6 ounces frozen orange-juice concentrate
</P>
<P>
   8 ounces ginger ale
</P>
<P>
   11-ounce can mandarin oranges
</P>
<P>
   Dissolve the gelatins in the boiling water. Add the frozen
orange juice and stir until it melts. Add the ginger ale. You can
either add the mandarin oranges right away, or just add the juice
first and the oranges after the gelatin has started to thicken.
Either way, it is beautiful when allowed to chill in a ring mold.
Refrigerate until congealed.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 138 calories, trace fat, 27
grams carbohydrates, 8 grams protein, 0 cholesterol, 40 milligrams
sodium, trace of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Betty Washburn, Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   MOTHER'S NUTTY CREAM CHEESE SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4-6
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce package lime Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup boiling water
</P>
<P>
   8 ounces cream cheese
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups hot water
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons mayonnaise
</P>
<P>
   8-ounce can crushed pineapple
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped pecans
</P>
<P>
   Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water. In a separate bowl,
whip softened cream cheese, add Jell-O/water mixture slowly until
well-blended. Mix in mayonnaise until smooth. Add remaining
ingredients. Chill overnight.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 440 calories, 35 grams fat, 21
grams carbohydrates, 13 grams protein, 66 milligrams cholesterol,
243 milligrams sodium, 72 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Nancy Peet Gilbert and Cleone Peet, Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   CRANBERRY JELL-O SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8-10
</P>
<P>
   1 pound fresh cranberries
</P>
<P>
   2 cups water
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   2 (3 ounces each) package orange Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups chopped celery
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chopped walnuts
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups crushed, drained pineapple
</P>
<P>
   Cook cranberries with water and sugar until they pop in their
jackets. Add Jell-O to the cranberry mixture. Then add the celery,
walnuts and pineapple. Mix and refrigerate to set.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 306 calories, 7 grams fat, 54
grams carbohydrates, 10 grams protein, 0 cholesterol, 45 milligrams
sodium, 22 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Kimberly M. Welch, Grapevine, Texas
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   CRANBERRY SALAD RING
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4-6
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce package raspberry Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   1 cup hot water
</P>
<P>
   15-ounce can whole-berry cranberry sauce
</P>
<P>
   8-ounce can crushed pineapple, undrained
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped pecans
</P>
<P>
   Black olives
</P>
<P>
   Dissolve Jell-O in the hot water. Add the whole-berry cranberry
sauce and stir thoroughly. Add the crushed pineapple and juice and
the pecans. Pour into a ring mold and chill until firm. When ready
to serve, unmold and fill the center with black olives.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 241 calories, 7 grams fat, 42
grams carbohydrates, 6 grams protein, 0 cholesterol, 44 milligrams
sodium, 25 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Joan Hallford, North Richland Hills
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   MANDARIN ORANGE FLUFF
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4-6
</P>
<P>
   1 pint small-curd cottage cheese
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce package orange Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   15-ounce can crushed pineapple, drained
</P>
<P>
   11-ounce can mandarin oranges, drained
</P>
<P>
   8-ounce container nondairy whipped topping
</P>
<P>
   Combine cottage cheese and dry Jell-O. Mix well. Add crushed
pineapple.
</P>
<P>
   Mix well. Add oranges. Gently fold in topping. Refrigerate.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 267 calories, 10 grams fat, 31
grams carbohydrates, 14 grams protein, 3 milligrams cholesterol, 42
milligrams sodium, 34 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Joan Hallford, North Richland Hills
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   HOLIDAY JELL-O
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   1 3-ounce box each red, green and lemon (or pineapple, if you
can find it) Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   1 1/4 cup pineapple juice (add water if not enough)
</P>
<P>
   1 cup crushed pineapple, drained and packed in own juice
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup miniature marshmallows
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup mayonnaise
</P>
<P>
   8-ounce container frozen nondairy topping
</P>
<P>
   Make red Jell-O using 1 1/4 cups boiling water; stir until
dissolved. Pour into a 7-by-11-inch glass cake pan. Place in
refrigerator until set.
</P>
<P>
   Bring 1 1/4 cups pineapple juice to boil. Add lemon Jell-O,
pineapples, marshmallows, and mayonnaise, and stir until everything
is melted and dissolved. Stir in the topping. Place in refrigerator
until set.
</P>
<P>
   Make green Jell-O using 1 1/4 cup boiling water; stir until
dissolved. Pour over top of pineapple layer. Let sit until solid.
Cut into squares to serve.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 167 calories, 9 grams fat, 19
grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 3 milligrams cholesterol, 51
milligrams sodium, 48 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Helen L. Folger, Richland Hills
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   MRS. ROBINSON'S TOMATO ASPIC
</P>
<P>
   Serves 2-4
</P>
<P>
   15-ounce can RoTel tomatoes
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce package lemon Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon cider vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   Combine ingredients in saucepan. Heat until Jell-O has
dissolved. Pour back into the RoTel can. Refrigerate until
congealed. Using can opener, open sealed bottom of can and push
cylinder onto plate. Use can marks as cutting guides.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 103 calories, 1 gram fat, 18
grams carbohydrates, 8 grams protein, 0 cholesterol, 208 milligrams
sodium, 4 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Martha Robinson, Farmers Branch, Texas
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   WILD CHERRY JELL-O
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4-6
</P>
<P>
   16- to 20-ounce can Queen Anne pitted sweet cherries
</P>
<P>
   3-ounce package wild cherry Jell-O
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup port
</P>
<P>
   11-ounce can mandarin oranges
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped walnuts
</P>
<P>
   Heat 1 cup juice from cherries and dissolve the Jell-O in it.
Add wine. Cool until it starts to set. Add drained oranges and
cherries. Fold in nuts. Pour into a ring mold that has been sprayed
with non-stick spray.
</P>
<P>
   Dressing:
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup mayonnaise
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon orange zest
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons heavy cream
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 303 calories, 18 grams fat, 26
grams carbohydrates, 9 grams protein, 17 milligrams cholesterol, 96
milligrams sodium, 53 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Kathleen Henderson, Granbury, Texas
</P>
