<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19981118.0199 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-18 16:17 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7044 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-VIDEO-MINIS19-COX     11-18 0214
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-MINIS19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mini movie views
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas'' (R) _ The kind of movie
you'll love or hate, depending on your mood. Johnny Depp and
Benicio Del Toro tear through the neon desert, high on anything
they can get. Directed with hallucinatory flair by Terry Gilliam
(``12 Monkeys''), it's both a tribute to and a cautionary tale
about excess. With Christina Ricci as a waifish Barbra Streisand
fan who has a bad trip. Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Can't Hardly Wait'' (PG-13) _ You won't want to wait. . .
for the movie to end. This teen comedy about an
end-of-the-school-year all-night party shirks subtlety whenever a
broad stroke will get us there faster. Jennifer Love Hewitt plays
Amanda, the goddess of the just-graduated senior class. Ethan Embry
is the sweet, sensitive guy who, the movie tries to convince us,
deserves to be her boyfriend. Grade: C
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Land Girls'' (R) _ Catherine McCormack, Rachel Weisz and
Anna Friel star in this tepid British weepy about three women who
spend World War II in the countryside. There, they help grow food
and fall in and out of tedious romances. Grade: C
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
