<HEADLINE>
LACK OF TRUCK INSPECTION OFFICERS KEEPS TEXAS ON DANGEROUS COURSE
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanied by TRUCKS-SAFETY) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By G. CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   GARLAND, Texas _ The 18-wheeler just wouldn't stop, despite the
red lights flashing and siren blasting on the highway patrol car
riding close behind it.
</P>
<P>
   The truck continued for a mile or two, gradually slowing.
Finally, when it was down to a crawl, the driver jumped out and
threw a log in front of the rear wheels, stopping the vehicle.
