<P>
   LOBBYISTS _ WASHINGTON _ Pity the poor lobbyist. In a new survey
of members of the American League of Lobbyists, 62 percent agreed
that ``the lobbying profession is unfairly maligned because of a
general lack of public understanding.'' Still, many of the
professional persuaders have other consolations: 65 percent of the
league's members reported earning more than $100,000 a year.
(Mollison, Cox News Service).
