<P>
   WOEFUL-BENGALS _ CINCINNATI _ When it comes to X's and O's, the
Cincinnati offense is a virtual mirror image of the offenses used
by Denver, Green Bay, Minnesota and San Francisco. When it comes to
W's and L's, the Bengals are in a class by themselves, a class
woefully short of star pupils. While the leading proponents of the
West Coast offense are gearing up for the playoffs, Cincinnati, 2-8
heading into Sunday's home game with Baltimore, is gearing down for
an eighth straight losing season. (Williams, Dayton Daily News)
