   AIRCAP-TRAVEL-AGENTS (Los Angeles) _ A year after the nation's
airlines angered travel agents by capping commissions for domestic
flights, agents were notified by United last week that a cap is now
in place on international flights. American has followed suit with
a $100 cap on commissions, and agents fear the rest of the airlines
are sure to follow. By Enrique Rivero.
