<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COKE-HOLIDAYADS19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Coca-Cola, Pepsi thirsting for extra sales during holidays
 &HT;    By Mickey H. Gramig
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Coca-Cola and rival Pepsico are pouring out holiday
promotions designed to pump up year-end sales.
</P>
<P>
   The six weeks between Thanksgiving and New Year's account for
about 15 percent of annual soft drink sales, said Gary Hemphill,
vice president of information services at Beverage Marketing Corp.
</P>
<P>
   While that surge in holiday sales isn't as big as it is for
wine, beer and spirits, it's enough of an increase to generate
increased marketing efforts and aggressive price promotions,
Hemphill said.
</P>
<P>
   At Atlanta-based Coca-Cola, activities run the gamut from a
discount card to a phone card giveaway, rounded out by cyber-deals.
Highlights include:
</P>
<P>
   _ The Coca-Cola/Give Kids the World Holiday Discount Card. The
card, available for $1.99 at Kmart stores nationwide, offers more
than $125 in discounts, including free popcorn with the purchase of
any Coca-Cola product at AMC Theatres, a second night free at
participating Holiday Inn hotels, $25 off selected American
Airlines flights and five minutes in free calling time on AT&AMP;T.
Coca-Cola will donate proceeds to Give Kids the World, an
Orlando-based group that grants dream vacations to kids with
life-threatening illnesses.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Gift of Refreshment. This five-minute AT&AMP;T calling card is
attached to several million 32- and 40-ounce cups at selected
fountain locations, including Circle K and Texaco convenience
stores.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Coca-Cola Holiday Web site, at http://www.coke.com.
Surfers get the site's password behind labels of 20-ounce or
one-liter bottles of Coca-Cola Classic. Then they can order
Coca-Cola's holiday CD for $3.98, featuring performers such as
Marcy Playground, Ever Clear and Boyz II Men singing trendy
versions of classic Christmas carols. The site also is filled with
activities, letting visitors do such things as create, send and
receive holiday e-cards, post their wish lists or place themselves
on the naughty or nice page._ Locally, ``Coke on Ice'' again takes
center stage outside the World of Coca-Cola, adjacent to
Underground Atlanta. The Southeast's largest outdoor ice skating
rink will be open Nov. 27-Jan. 3. (For details, call 404-676-5151.)
</P>
<P>
   Pepsico's holiday marketing centers on two promotions:
</P>
<P>
   _ An under-the-cap game where 300,000 consumers will win ``party
packages'' filled with $40 in free Pepsi and Frito-Lay products.
</P>
<P>
   _ And ``Santa's House Party,'' another joint campaign with
Frito-Lay that will flood the marketplace with more than 50 million
coupons for the company's soft drinks and Wow! snacks.
</P>
<P>
   Pepsico hasn't announced plans to run new holiday-themed
commercials, and New Year's marketing efforts are still under
wraps, said spokesman Brad Shaw.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
