<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Saint Ted?
 &HT;    By Richard L. Eldredge
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Ted Turner's musings on a possible run for president weren't the
only surprise in this week's New Yorker magazine profile. Turner
also confirmed tabloid reports that he and wife Jane Fonda have
been seeing a marriage counselor.
</P>
<P>
   At the recent Nuclear Age Peace Foundation dinner in California,
the magazine quotes Turner as telling fellow diners: ``We just came
from a marriage counselor in Santa Monica. Jane wants me to become
a saint _ but I'm not.''
</P>
<P>
   A bauble for Betty
</P>
<P>
   At the risk of blowing the surprise, Buzz is pleased to report
that Smyrna (Ga.) mom Betty Motes is getting a sapphire heart
necklace from Tiffany's for her birthday. Daughter and actress
Julia Roberts picked out the trinket recently while shopping for
Motes in New York.
</P>
<P>
   ``Oh, I think it's beautiful,'' Roberts reportedly told the
sales staff. ``This is for my mom and I want it to be perfect.''
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: buzz(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   For more juicy gossip and keen commentary, see what Vixana has
to say on ajc.com.
</P>
