A7851 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LITERARY-QUIZ-TEX     11-18 0506
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LITERARY-QUIZ-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here's another they-did-and-they-didn't quiz, focused on authors
born in November. You pass with nine correct answers (a simple
majority) and earn an A with 12 right. Answers are on the opposite
page.
</P>
<P>
   1. Hermann Hesse wrote (a) ``Siddhartha;'' (b) ``Steppenwolf;''
(c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   2. Franz Kafka wrote (a) ``The Castle;'' (b) ``The Trial;'' (c)
both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   3. Nathaniel Hawthorne wrote (a) ``The Talisman;'' (b) ``The
Marble Faun;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   4. Marcel Proust wrote (a) ``Within a Budding Grove;'' (b)
``Under the Greenwood Tree;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of
the above.
</P>
<P>
   5. E.B. White wrote (a) ``Stuart Little;'' (b) ``The Trumpet of
the Swan;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   6. Henry David Thoreau wrote (a) ``Common Sense;'' (b) ``Mosses
From an Old Manse;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the
above.
</P>
<P>
   7. Isaac Bashevis Singer wrote (a) ``The Brothers Ashkenazi;''
(b) ``The Family Moskat;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of
the above.
</P>
<P>
   8. Iris Murdoch wrote (a) ``The Prime of Miss Jean Brodie;'' (b)
``The Bull From the Sea;'' (b) both of the above; (d) neither of
the above.
</P>
<P>
   9. William Makepeace Thackeray wrote (a) ``Barry Lyndon;'' (b)
``Daniel Deronda;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the
above.
</P>
<P>
   10. Clifford Odets wrote (a) ``The Country Girl;'' (b) ``Golden
Boy;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   11. Hart Crane wrote (a) ``A Bridge Too Far;'' (b) ``White
Buildings;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   12. Ernest Hemingway wrote (a) ``The Beautiful and Damned;'' (b)
``Of Time and the River;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of
the above.
</P>
<P>
   13. Stephen Vincent Benet wrote (a) ``John Brown's Body;'' (b)
``Spoon River Anthology;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of
the above.
</P>
<P>
   14. George Bernard Shaw wrote (a) ``Colonel Blimp;'' (b) ``Major
Barbara;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   15. Booth Tarkington wrote (a) ``Alice of Old Vincennes;'' (b)
``Magnificent Obsession;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of
the above.
</P>
<P>
   16. Emily Bronte wrote (a) ``Agnes Grey;'' (b) ``Shirley;'' (c)
both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
Quiz answers: 1-c; 2-c; 3-b; 4-a; 5-c; 6-d; 7-b; 8-d; 9-a; 10-c;
11-b; 12-d; 13-a; 14-b; 15-d; 16-d. True authors of works whose
authors are misidentified above are, in order: Washington Irving,
Thomas Hardy, Tom Paine, Nathaniel Hawthorne, Israel Joshua Singer,
Muriel Spark, Mary Renault, George Eliot, Cornelius Ryan, F. Scott
Fitzgerald, Thomas Wolfe, Edgar Lee Masters, Michael Powell and
Emeric Pressburger, Maurice Thompson, Lloyd C. Douglas, Anne
Bronte, and Charlotte Bronte..MDBR/.MDNM/
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
