   (NYT27) NEW ORLEANS -- Nov. 18, 1998 -- GOVS, 11-18 -- In their
debut appearance as heirs to the latest American political dynasty,
Gov. George Bush of Texas, right, and his brother, governor-elect
Jeb Bush of Florida, at the opening of the Republican Governors
Association's annual convention Wednesday in New Orleans. Not since
1967 -- when Nelson Rockefeller was governor of New York and his
brother Winthrop was governor of Arkansas -- have two brothers
occupied governor's mansions. (Lee Celano/New York Times Photo)
</P>
