<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-18 23:15 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8253 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBC-SECREPORT19-COX     11-18 1555
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-SECREPORT19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mississippi State LB Carroll cleared to play
 &HT;    By Tony Barnhart and Wendy Parker
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ ALABAMA vs. Auburn, Saturday, 7:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   After sitting out Saturday's Mississippi State game, linebacker
Travis Carroll has been cleared to play. Carroll has been dealing
with a shoulder injury since preseason. ... In four road games this
season, Alabama has been outscored 51-9 in the first half. The
Crimson Tide trailed 17-0 at halftime last week against Mississippi
State. In fact, Alabama did not score a TD in the first half of any
of its road games. ... Alabama has given up just three turnovers in
its last 17 quarters of play. ... QB Andrew Zow needs 222 yards
passing against Auburn to become the fifth player in school history
to throw for more than 2,000 in a season. ... SS Tony Dixon had 14
tackles against Mississippi State, giving him 25 over his last two
games. ... Alabama has a five-game winning streak over Auburn at
Legion Field.
</P>
<P>
   ARKANSAS at Miss. State, Saturday, 12:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Arkansas coaches said they were under the impression that a
player could ``get rid'' of the ball, as punter Chris Akin did
against Tennessee when he kicked the ball out of the end zone, but
that the rules don't specify methods allowed. The league said
Tennessee should have had the option of getting the ball or taking
the safety.... Representatives from the Sugar and Cotton bowls will
be in Starkville on Saturday. Arkansas would earn a berth in the
Sugar Bowl if it reaches the SEC Championship game, or the Cotton
if Mississippi State wins the SEC West. ... The two touchdown
catches by Anthony Lucas against Tennessee set an Arkansas career
mark. Lucas, who now has 17, also established a single-season mark
with nine.
</P>
<P>
   AUBURN at Alabama, Saturday, 7:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Freshman quarterback Gabe Gross continues to be bothered by a
shoulder injury suffered last Saturday against Georgia. Gross,
however, is expected to play Saturday. ... Linebacker Tavarreus
Pounds, who also has a shoulder injury, is still uncertain. With
all the problems Auburn had this season, a win over Alabama would
ease a lot of the pain. ``I guarantee, if we win, a lot of people
will forget about our troubles this season,'' defensive tackle
Charles Dorsey said. ... Receiver Karsten Bailey now has 142 career
catches, breaking the school record of 141 held by Terry Beasley.
Bailey caught nine passes for 114 yards in last week's game against
Georgia. . . . Auburn has intercepted at least one pass in six
consecutive games. The Tigers have seven interceptions in the last
two games.
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA at Florida State, Saturday, 3:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Defensive tackle Reggie McGrew continues to be bothered by a bad
back, which has kept him out of the last two games. But he said he
can't give his back any more time to heal and will not miss
Saturday's game. ``I gave it as long as it's going to get,'' McGrew
said. ``It's time to go.'' ... Defensive end Willie Cohens still
has bone fragments in as knee but passed on surgery in order to
play. The other end, Tim Beauchamp, has a sprained ankle but also
will play. ... Coach Steve Spurrier said the Gators will try as
many as seven new players on the kickoff-coverage team. ... After
taking a beating against South Carolina, QB Doug Johnson probably
will start the game in the shotgun. ... RB Terry Jackson, who has
an ankle , is expected to play.
</P>
<P>
   KENTUCKY at Tennessee, Saturday, 3:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   The Wildcats practiced Wednesday night so players could attend
the funeral of Christopher Scott Brock, a boyhood friend of QB Tim
Couch who was killed with UK defensive lineman Arthur Steinmetz in
a traffic accident. The team is scheduled to travel by bus this
morning to Somerset, Ky., for the funeral of Steinmetz, who was
sitting out the season after transferring from Michigan State. ...
All players, coaches and school officials are abiding by a gag rule
against commenting on manslaughter and drunken-driving charges
against center Jason Watts, who remains hospitalized. Watts, the
driver in the accident, was 1 1/2 times over the state
blood-alcohol limit of .10, police said. ... WR Quentin McCord
returned to practice Tuesday for the first time since spraining an
ankle against Georgia and is listed as probable.
</P>
<P>
   LSU at Notre Dame, Saturday, 1:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Gerry DiNardo is playing down his return to Notre Dame,
where he was an All-American guard on the Irish's national title
team of 1973. Instead, he thinks his team (4-5) can still qualify
for a bowl if it can win its final two games with Notre Dame and
Arkansas. ``If you had watched Sunday's practice, you would not
know this was a 4-5 team that was supposed to be much better than
it was,'' DiNardo said. ... DE Arnold Miller says that, after
beating Notre Dame 27-9 in the Fiesta Bowl, the Tigers are not in
awe of the Irish. The two teams also met earlier last season, with
Notre Dame winning 24-6. ``Since we played them twice before, we
know we can dominate them,'' Miller said. ... Defensive tackle
Anthony McFarland needs four sacks in his last two games to set the
LSU season record. McFarland has eight.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI at Georgia, Saturday, 1 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   The Rebels spent the off week trying to shore up their
secondary, which was torched Nov. 7 against Arkansas. Receiver Ken
Lucas has been spending some time at cornerback. ... In the '90s,
Ole Miss has split its eight meetings with Georgia. ... Since the
SEC went to divisional play in 1992, Ole Miss is 11-9 against teams
from the SEC East. Coach Tommy Tuberville is 7-4 against the other
division. ... Tuberville's 25 wins in his first 43 games at Ole
Miss is the second-best start for a coach in school history. John
Vaught was 29-13-1 in his 43 games in Oxford. ... Saturday's game
will be a homecoming for AD John Shafer, who was on Georgia's staff
for 16 years. ... Assistant Hugh Nall was a center on Georgia's
national championship team in 1980. Graduate assistant Scott
McDuffie played briefly for Georgia.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE vs. Arkansas, Saturday, 12:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   For the third year in a row, the Bulldogs have a chance to win
the SEC West. But the Razorbacks have dashed their hopes both
previous times. An MSU win would forge a tie with Arkansas, and it
could clinch with a win over Ole Miss. ... Lost in James Johnson's
showing last week as SEC offensive player of the week was that he
got 87 of his school-record 237 rushing yards in the fourth quarter
against the Crimson Tide. His 312 all-purpose yards also are a
school mark ... QB Wayne Madkin's numbers have improved so much
over the last four games _ 41-for-74 passing, 715 yards, six TDs
and one interception _ that offensive coordinator Lynn Amedee has
returned to his booth in the press box. He had been on the field
while Madkin, a redshirt freshman, was learning.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH CAROLINA at Clemson, Saturday, 6:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   The Gamecocks can't erase their 1-9 record, but players and
coaches agree that a win over Clemson would make the offseason a
little nicer. ``This game stands on its own,'' coach Brad Scott
said. ... Linebacker Willie Offord has a sprained knee and might
not play. ... South Carolina finished winless (0-8) in the SEC for
the first time since joining the conference in 1992. ... Tailback
Boo Williams left the Florida game with a turf toe but is expected
to play Saturday. ... Williams returned four kickoffs for 109 yards
against the Gators. South Carolina and Kentucky have attempted more
fourth-down conversions (26) than any teams in the SEC. South
Carolina has made 15 of the attempts.
</P>
<P>
   TENNESSEE vs. Kentucky, Saturday, 3:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Linebacker Al Wilson is still suffering from a pulled groin but
is expected to play. Others among others nursing injuries are
linebackers Raynoch Thompson (bruised knee) and Eric Westmoreland
(ribs), receiver Peerless Price (ribs) and cornerback Steve Johnson
(concussion). All are expected to play. ... Tennessee's goal is to
hold Kentucky's offense to less than 300 yards and 17 points.
That's the goal for every game the Vols play. The Wildcats had 634
yards in last season's game with Tennessee. ... Tennessee has won
17 regular-season and 14 home games in a row. ... TB Travis Henry
now has run for more than 100 yards in three of his last four
games. ... Tennessee is 9-2 in its last 11 games against ranked
teams, including 4-0 this season.
</P>
<P>
   VANDERBILT vs. Tennessee, Nov. 28
</P>
<P>
   Coach Woody Widenhofer said his offensive line has improved and
played a solid game in last week's 55-17 loss to Kentucky. The
Commodores did reel off a number of impressive big plays: a 50-yard
run by Jared McGrath, a 73-yard TD pass from Greg Zolman to Tavarus
Hogans _ Vandy's longest of the season _ and a 96-yard kickoff
return for a TD by Jimmy Williams. RB Lew Thomas also gained 51
yards on the ground. ... Zolman, who aggravated a shoulder in the
Kentucky game and was lifted for David Wallace, is expected to be
ready. But CB Fred Vinson (sprained foot) won't return to practice
until Sunday and might be questionable for the last game of his
college career. Vinson, a pre-season All-American, has missed parts
of three games with injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
