<SLUG> BC-PHARMANEX-SALES-SHIFT-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NUTRITIONAL SUPPLEMENTS MAKER SHIFTING TO DIRECT SALES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEN SULLIVAN  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- Nutritional supplements maker Pharmanex Inc. said
it has begun pulling all of its products from store shelves as it
shifts to a new direct-sales model.
</P>
<P>
   The move follows Pharmanex's purchase this summer by Provo,
Utah-based Nu Skin Enterprises, a multilevel marketer, which will
begin selling the suburban Simi Valley company's herbal and dietary
supplements through independent sales contractors. The transition
should be complete by Jan. 15, a company spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
   The move is ``calculated to take advantage of the growth in
direct sales in the United States,'' Pharmanex President Bill
McGlashan said in a written statement. McGlashan said direct
selling ``represents a more attractive way to differentiate the
benefits . . . of Pharmanex products.''
</P>
<P>
   Nu Skin Chief Executive Steven Lund described the shift as ``the
logical next step'' in the integration of Pharmanex into the Nu
Skin organization. The company said Pharmanex products such as
green tea capsules and the cholesterol-lowering yeast product
Cholestin will be available for sale by Nu Skin's approximately
500,000 sales representatives internationally, though the reps are
not required to carry the products.
</P>
<P>
   Both Nu Skin and Pharmanex have come under government scrutiny
in the last year. The U.S. Food and Drug Administration is trying
to prevent the firm from selling Cholestin, insisting that its
contents constitute a drug and require government approval. A
federal judge is currently considering the complaint.
</P>
<P>
   And in February, the Pennsylvania Attorney General's Office
accused Nu Skin of operating a pyramid scheme related to the sale
of electricity services. Nu Skin later settled those charges with
the state while denying the charges.
</P>
<P>
   XXX
</P>
</TEXT>
